image.caption: Thousands gathered at the Federal Courthouse in down Eugene, Ore., for the 2nd annual Women's March calling attention to equal rights and equality for women on Saturday, Jan. 20, 2018. (Collin Andrew/The Register-Guard)
Thousands fill the courtyard and streets in front of the Wayne L. Morse U.S. Courthouse in Eugene for the Women’s March for Action. (Chris Pietsch/The Register-Guard)

Eleven-year-old Indiana Setter (right) and her sister Sabine Setter, 9, document the thousands that filled the courtyard and streets in front of the Wayne L. Morse U.S. Courthouse in Eugene, Ore., for the Women’s March for Action on Saturday, Jan. 20, 2018. The Setter's who attended last years Women's March to have their voice heard, instead brought their cameras to focus on the process of listening. (Collin Andrew/The Register-Guard)

Representing the 4th District of Oregon, Congressman Peter DeFazio speaks to a crowd of thousands via cell phone highlighting equal rights and equality for women on Saturday, Jan. 20, 2018. DeFazio was unable able to attend the rally due to the U.S. Government shutdown. (Collin Andrew/The Register-Guard)
